Item management and order line total calculation
Alarms when a payment gateway is down
Purchase validation against pre-paid balance / credit limit
Ageing for customers with overdue invoices
Calculates the order total and the total for each line, considering the item prices, the quantity and if the prices are percentage or not.
Adds an additional line to the order with a percentage charge to represent the value added tax.
A very simple implementation that sets the due date of the invoice. The due date is calculated by just adding the period of time to the invoice date.

This task will copy all the lines on the orders and invoices to the new invoice, considering the periods involved for each order, but not the fractions of periods. It will not copy the lines that are taxes. The quantity and total of each line will be multiplied by the amount of periods.
Decides if an order should be included in an invoice for a given billing process. This is done by taking the billing process time span, the order period, the active since/until, etc.
Always returns true, meaning that the overdue invoice will be carried over to a new invoice.
Calculates the start and end period to be included in an invoice. This is done by taking the billing process time span, the order period, the active since/until, etc.
Integration with the authorize.net payment gateway.
Notifies a user by sending an email. It supports text and HTML emails
Finds the information of a payment method available to a customer, given priority to credit card. In other words, it will return the credit car of a customer or the ACH information in that order.
Will generate a PDF version of an invoice.
Returns always false, which makes jBilling to never carry over an invoice into another newer invoice.
Will create a new order with a penalty item. The item is taken as a parameter to the task.
Extends BasicOrderFilterTask, modifying the dates to make the order applicable a number of months before it would be by using the default filter.
Extends BasicOrderPeriodTask, modifying the dates to make the order applicable a number of months before itd be by using the default task.
Extends the standard authorize.net payment processor to also send an email to the company after processing the payment.
Sends an email to the billing administrator as an alarm when a payment gateway is down.
A test payment processor implementation to be able to test jBillings functions without using a real payment gateway.
Router payment processor based on Custom Fields
Allows a customer to be assigned a specific payment gateway. It checks a custom contact field to identify the gateway and then delegates the actual payment processing to another plugin.
It determines how a payment event affects the subscription status of a user, considering its present status and a state machine.
Integration with the ACH commerce payment gateway.
A dummy task that does not add any parameters for asynchronous payment processing. This is the default.
This plug-in adds parameters for asynchronous payment processing to have one processing message bean per payment processor. It is used in combination with the router payment processor plug-ins.
It adds items to an order. If the item is already in the order, it only updates the quantity.

This is a rules-based plug-in. It will do what the basic item manager does (actually calling it); but then it will execute external rules as well. These external rules have full control on changing the order that is getting new items.
This is a rules-based plug-in. It calculates the total for an order line (typically this is the price multiplied by the quantity); allowing for the execution of external rules.

This is a rules-based plug-in. It gives a price to an item by executing external rules. You can then add logic externally for pricing. It is also integrated with the mediation process by having access to the mediation pricing data.
This is a reader for the mediation process. It reads records from a text file whose fields are separated by a character (or string).

This is a rules-based plug-in (see chapter 7). It takes an event record from the mediation process and executes external rules to translate the record into billing meaningful data. This is at the core of the mediation component, see the ?Telecom Guide? document for more information.
This is a reader for the mediation process. It reads records from a text file whose fields have fixed positions,and the record has a fixed length.

This is exactly the same as the standard payment information task, the only difference is that it does not validate if the credit card is expired. Use this plug-in only if you want to submit payment with expired credit cards.
This plug-in is only used for testing purposes. Instead of sending an email (or other real notification); it simply stores the text to be sent in a file named emails_sent.txt.
Order periods calculator with pro rating.
This plugin takes into consideration the field cycle starts of orders to calculate fractional order periods.
Invoice composition task with pro-rating (day as fraction)
When creating an invoice from an order, this plug-in will pro-rate any fraction of a period taking a day as the smallest billable unit.
Payment process for the Intraanuity payment gateway
Integration with the Intraanuity payment gateway.
This plug-in will create a new order with a negative price to reflect a credit when an order is canceled within a period that has been already invoiced.
Fees for early cancellation of a plan.
This plug-in will use external rules to determine if an order that is being canceled should create a new order with a penalty fee. This is typically used for early cancels of a contract.
Used for blocking payments from reaching real payment processors. Typically configured as first payment processor in the processing chain.
Blacklist user when their status becomes suspended or higher.
Causes users and their associated details (e.g., credit card number, phone number, etc.) to be blacklisted when their status becomes suspended or higher.
This is a reader for the mediation process. It reads records from a JDBC database source.
This is a reader for the mediation process. It is an extension of the JDBC reader, allowing easy configuration of a MySQL database source.
Responds to order related events. Runs rules to generate commands to send via JMS messages to the external provisioning module.
This plug-in is only used for testing purposes. It is a test external provisioning task for testing the provisioning modules.
An external provisioning plug-in for communicating with the Ericsson Customer Administration Interface (CAI).
Delegates the actual payment processing to another plug-in based on the currency of the payment.
An external provisioning plug-in for communicating with the TeliaSonera MMSC.
Filters out negative invoices for carry over.
This filter will only invoices with a positive balance to be carried over to the next invoice.
It will generate a file with one line per invoice generated.
It will call a package of rules when an internal event happens.
It will update the dynamic balance of a customer (pre-paid or credit limit) when events affecting the balance happen.
Balance validator based on the customer balance.
Used for real-time mediation, this plug-in will validate a call based on the current dynamic balance of a customer.
Used for real-time mediation, this plug-in will validate a call based on a package or rules
Integration with the Payments Gateway payment processor.
Saves the credit card information in the payment gateway, rather than the jBilling DB.

This is a rules-based plug-in compatible with the mediation module of jBilling 2.2.x. It will do what the basic item manager does (actually calling it); but then it will execute external rules as well. These external rules have full control on changing the order that is getting new items.

This is a rules-based plug-in, compatible with the mediation process of jBilling 2.2.x and later. It calculates the total for an order line (typically this is the price multiplied by the quantity); allowing for the execution of external rules.

This is a rules-based plug-in compatible with the mediation module of jBilling 2.2.x. It gives a price to an item by executing external rules. You can then add logic externally for pricing. It is also integrated with the mediation process by having access to the mediation pricing data.
Test payment processor for external storage.
A fake plug-in to test payments that would be stored externally.
Payment processor plug-in to integrate with RBS WorldPay
Payment processor plug-in to integrate with RBS WorldPay. It stores the credit card information (number, etc) in the gateway.
Monitors the balance of a customer and upon reaching a limit, it requests a real-time payment
Payment processor for integration with the Beanstream payment gateway
Payment processor for integration with the Sage payment gateway
Called when the billing process runs to select which users to evaluate. This basic implementation simply returns every user not in suspended (or worse) status
Called when the billing process runs to select which users to evaluate. This only returns users with orders that have a next invoice date earlier than the billing process.
Event records with errors are saved to a file
Event records with errors are saved to a database table
Submits payments to paypal as a payment gateway and stores credit card information in PayPal as well
Submits payments to authorize.net as a payment gateway and stores credit card information in authorize.net as well
Delegates the actual payment processing to another plug-in based on the payment method of the payment.
Generates rules dynamically based on a Velocity template.
A scheduled task to execute the Mediation Process.
A scheduled task to execute the Billing Process.
Ages a user based on the number of days that the account is overdue.
A scheduled task to execute the Ageing Process.
Ages a user based on the number of business days (excluding holidays) that the account is overdue.

Total amount invoiced grouped by period.
Detailed balance ageing report. Shows the age of outstanding customer balances.
Number of users subscribed to a specific product.
Total payment amount received grouped by period.
Number of customers created within a period.
Total revenue (sum of received payments) per customer.
Simple accounts receivable report showing current account balances.
General ledger details of all invoiced charges for the given day.
General ledger summary of all invoiced charges for the given day, grouped by item type.
Attach PDF invoice to email notification.
Add order Id to invoice lines.
Allow customers to edit own contact information.
Link ageing to customer subscriber status.
Lock-out user after failed login attempts.
Grace period in days before ageing a customer with an overdue invoice.
Partner default percentage commission rate. See the Partner section of the documentation.
Partner default flat fee to be paid as commission. See the Partner section of the documentation.
Set to '1' to enable one-time payment for partners. If set, partners will only get paid once per customer. See the Partner section of the documentation.
Partner default payout period unit. See the Partner section of the documentation.
Partner default payout period value. See the Partner section of the documentation.
Set to '1' to enable batch payment payouts using the billing process and the configured payment processor. See the Partner section of the documentation.
Partner default assigned clerk id. See the Partner section of the documentation.
Currency ID to use when paying partners. See the Partner section of the documentation.
Set to '1' to e-mail invoices as the billing company. '0' to deliver invoices as jBilling.
Set to '1' to show notes in invoices, '0' to disable.
Days before the orders 'active until' date to send the 1st notification. Leave blank to disable.
Days before the orders 'active until' date to send the 2nd notification. Leave blank to disable.
Days before the orders 'active until' date to send the 3rd notification. Leave blank to disable.
Prefix value for generated invoice public numbers.
The current value for generated invoice public numbers. New invoices will be assigned a public number by incrementing this value.
Set to '1' to allow invoices to be deleted, '0' to disable.
Set to '1' to allow invoice reminder notifications, '0' to disable.
Set to '1' to enable, '0' to disable.
Set to '1' to enable the billing process to calculate interest on overdue payments, '0' to disable. Calculation of interest is handled by the selected penalty plug-in.
Set to '1' to use the 'OrderFilterAnticipateTask' to invoice a number of months in advance, '0' to disable. Plug-in must be configured separately.

A URL where the graphic of the PayPal button resides. The button is displayed to customers when they are making a payment. The default is usually the best option, except when another language is needed.
URL for the HTTP Callback to invoke when the ageing process changes a status of a user.

Default '2000-01-01'. If this preference is used, the system will make sure that all your invoices have their dates in a incremental way. Any invoice with a greater 'ID' will also have a greater (or equal) date. In other words, a new invoice can not have an earlier date than an existing (older) invoice. To use this preference, set it as a string with the date where to start.
Set to '1' to attach a PDF version of the invoice to all invoice notification e-mails. '0' to disable.
Set to '1' to show the 'include in separate invoice' flag on an order. '0' to disable.

Set to '1' to include the ID of the order in the description text of the resulting invoice line. '0' to disable. This can help to easily track which exact orders is responsible for a line in an invoice, considering that many orders can be included in a single invoice.
Set to '1' to allow customers to edit their own contact information. '0' to disable.
Set to '1' to mask all credit card numbers. '0' to disable. When set, numbers are masked to all users, even administrators, and in all log files.
Set to '1' to change the subscription status of a user when the user ages. '0' to disable.
The number of retries to allow before locking the user account. A locked user account will have their password changed to the value of lockout_password in the jbilling.properties configuration file.
If greater than zero, it represents the number of days that a password is valid. After those days, the password is expired and the user is forced to change it.
Set to '1' to allow the usage of the 'main subscription' flag for orders This flag is read only by the mediation process when determining where to place charges coming from external events.

Set to '1' to allow the use of pro-rating to invoice fractions of a period. Shows the 'cycle' attribute of an order. Note that you need to configure the corresponding plug-ins for this feature to be fully functional.
If the payment blacklist feature is used, this is set to the id of the configuration of the PaymentFilterTask plug-in. See the Blacklist section of the documentation.
Set to '1' to allow negative payments. '0' to disable

Set to '1' to delay payment of negative invoice amounts, causing the balance to be carried over to the next invoice. Invoices that have had negative balances from other invoices transferred to them are allowed to immediately make a negative payment (credit) if needed. '0' to disable. Preference 44 & 46 are usually also enabled.

Set to '1' to allow invoices with negative balances to generate a new invoice that isn't composed of any orders so that their balances will always get carried over to a new invoice for the credit to take place. '0' to disable. Preference 44 & 45 are usually also enabled.
ID of the last record read by the mediation process. This is used to determine what records are 'new' and need to be read.
Set to '1' to allow the use of provisioning. '0' to disable.

The threshold value for automatic payments. Pre-paid users with an automatic recharge value set will generate an automatic payment whenever the account balance falls below this threshold. Note that you need to configure the AutoRechargeTask plug-in for this feature to be fully functional.
